WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) _ Chatham Lodging Trust (CLDT) on Wednesday reported a key measure of profitability in its first quarter, after reporting a loss in the same period a year earlier. The results topped Wall Street expectations.The real estate investment trust, based in West Palm Beach, Florida, said it had funds from operations of $3.5 million, or 7 cents per share, in the period.The average estimate of three analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for a funds from operations loss of 1 cent per share.Funds from operations is a closely watched measure in the REIT industry. It takes net income and adds back items such as depreciation and amortization.The company said it had a loss of $11.4 million, or 23 cents per share.The real estate investment trust posted revenue of $54.9 million in the period, which also topped Street forecasts. Three analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $53.9 million.ADVERTISEMENT_____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on CLDT at https://www.zacks.com/ap/CLDT